{
  "stem": "22979.6",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, I, I gave it to, to, to Dan, which I'm very sorry.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But, you know, about that, the one woman, I have a picture book from, from--",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, 1944, like I said, it was the uprising ghetto sonderkommando.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The Hungarian transport stopped, but the killing didn't.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The killing went on in different ways, not massive, you know, transports with gassing.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they killed the people by shooting them in Auschwitz or in the woods there.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we went on doing regular our job, I mean, the 12 hour shift, you know, sorting the clothing.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The SS came more and more stealing clothing, and jewelery, and valuables.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we knew all because we found many times in, in their luggage newspapers with the newest, you know, what happened in the world, that the Russian's front is closer, the Allies already occupied quite almost, you know, all Europe, except Germany.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And so we always thought, you know, we-- maybe some of us will be so lucky to see the light, I would say.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But our hope was not too much, because the SS always assured us the only way is out through the chimney.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But you know how I said from the start, I wanted always to see a tomorrow.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Maybe tomorrow will be better.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And it was about, I think so, close to new year.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They-- we didn't have-- we came from the night shift.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And the day shift was already lined up outside.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And then we had to stop and line up.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And in front of the roll call was, were two nurses, and a table, and something they had in front.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And always, the first five in the row had to go through a table.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And they drew blood from each of us.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
